    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>An Open Border With Mexico?</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Nason Goldstein letter on Aug 24 editorial says Pres Clinton should remind Pres-elect Vicente Fox that Mexican citizens do not have right to violate US immigration laws</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Visas for Mexican Workers'' (editorial, Aug. 24):</p>
        <p>President Clinton should remind Vicente Fox, Mexico's president-elect, that Mexican citizens do not have a right to violate United States immigration laws. If the illegal Mexican immigrants wore fatigues, they would be seen as invaders. Other solutions to Mexico's rapidly expanding population should be considered.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Visas for Mexican Workers'' (editorial, Aug. 24):</p>
        <p>President Clinton should remind Vicente Fox, Mexico's president-elect, that Mexican citizens do not have a right to violate United States immigration laws. If the illegal Mexican immigrants wore fatigues, they would be seen as invaders. Other solutions to Mexico's rapidly expanding population should be considered.</p>
        <p>Mr. Clinton should also propose and offer to help Mexico to establish family planning programs.</p>
        <p>NASON GOLDSTEIN  Royal Palm Beach, Fla.  Aug. 24, 2000</p>
      </block>
